* Enterprise Recursive Servers (ERS)
-- ERS (Enterprise Recursive Servers) are basically a DoDIN DNS Proxy
-- ERS Data can be found in the DCO Splunk index "nipr_bind_dns"
-- ERS has logs for several different DNS query types (mostly A and PTR)
-- Primarily useful when searching based on resolved domain, or based on external observed IP
-- Pivot into ERS logs when you observe DNS traffic at the boundary from ERS servers; logs should show originating DoDIN IP
-- RPZ (Response Policy Zone) alerts can be found in Splunk index "niproob_quo_dns"
-- RPZ logs contain alerts related to mitigation actions taken by ERS
-- Analyst demonstrates understanding of ERS logs, location, and use
-- Analyst demonstrates understanding of ERS properties including mitigation actions that ERS can take (Blocking, Sinkholing, Blackholing)
-- Analyst demonstrates an understanding of RPZ logs, location, and how/when to use them

